main event: A man saw a large, bright object with small objects emerging from it near Jefferson City, Missouri in 1967.
interesting points: The object was over 300 feet across and showed no visible doors or openings, yet the small objects seemed to come out of the material of the object.
The small objects took off at extremely high speeds, with G-forces that would crush any known living thing.
The witness is hesitant to discuss the sighting with most people due to concerns about being perceived as unintelligent or losing his teaching and principal positions.
The witness has discussed the sighting with his professor friends, but not with the general public in his local area.
The Air Force has tentatively identified the sighting as a hot air balloon incident, but the witness and others dispute this explanation.
sighted object: a large, bright object with small objects emerging from it
witnesses: the witness, who is a school principal
